@enonumus

Clearly you don't understand interpolation. Using any tool to modify a video to correct the aspect ratio will re-interpolate the pixels. This was not a case of the wrong pixel aspect ratio as in NTSC 0.9 vs NTSC 1.2, this was a weird aspect ratio so yes, interpolation is the only solution and that is always a bad idea. So, thanks, but no thanks.

After downloading the sample of this torrent and realizing it was stretched, I went ahead and downloaded another torrent of the same movie instead.
